Commentary: appeal for caught behind and the umpire raises his finger late. But du Plessis reviews immediately. This was a ball just outside off, close to his body, and he tries to run it fine, but the ball goes to the keeper instead. Was there an edge on the way to the keeper? Doesn't look like, and maybe the sound came from bat hitting the pad, but there's also a second sound according to snicko when the ball is near the bat. Out or not? Umpire has a difficult call to make... and he gives it out! That's because the snicko showed sound when the bat wasn't near the pad. Great decision by umpire Shozab Raza. Zalmi lose a review
